pct (for Containers):

List all containers:

bash
Copy code
pct list
Start a container:

bash
Copy code
pct start <vmid>
Stop a container:

bash
Copy code
pct stop <vmid>
Get detailed information about a container:

bash
Copy code
pct status <vmid>
Enter the console of a container:

bash
Copy code
pct enter <vmid>
Create a new container from a template:

bash
Copy code
pct create <vmid> <template> --storage <storage> --net0 <model>,bridge=<bridge>
Clone a container:

bash
Copy code
pct clone <source_vm_id> <new_vm_id> --name <new_name>
Set the memory for a container:

bash
Copy code
pct set <vmid> --mem <memory_in_MB>
Set the CPU cores for a container:

bash
Copy code
pct set <vmid> --cores <number_of_cores>
Delete a container:

bash
Copy code
pct destroy <vmid>
qm (for Virtual Machines):

List all virtual machines:

bash
Copy code
qm list
Start a virtual machine:

bash
Copy code
